"{\"uid\": \"athens-times.com-2024-olympic-games-italys-objection-was-rejected-in-its-mens-semi-finals-hungary\", \"text\": \"Athens Times  -  The international wet track federation rejected Italy's objection, calling for the quarter-final to be repeated with Hungary for the men's tournament. Hungary defeated Italy, however the neighbors protested the referees' decision to expel Francesco Contemi, in the second eight minutes of the match, in a phase where the 21-year-old player shoots, scores and puts the hand down finds Silard Jansick in the eye, wounding him. The referees, after several minutes of examination of the video, decided to expel without replacing Condemi, although he seemed to have no intention of hitting his opponent. The Italians objected after the race ended, but as it was next it was rejected. The Italians fought the case, referring to the World Aquatics appeal committee. The latter met this morning and again rejected the Italian appeal, ratifying Hungary's quadrant qualification. Thus, the analytical program of semi-finals and ranking matches was set on Friday (9/8), with the national pole facing Australia for positions 5-8 at 19:00. Analyticalally the programme : IMMELLICians 15:35 Serbia-US 20:35 Hungary-Croatia POINTS 5-8 14:00 Italy-Spain 19:00 GREECE-Australia  Athens Times  News about Greece and the World.\"}"